Once we have these, we can assemble them into our final model. \{F_t, G, \cdot, \cdot\}
We care more about F, G, and less about the observational variance and some covariance also for the system where the
F is going to be an F that has, you just concatenate the two Fs. Youâ€™re going to get 1, 0 and then youâ€™re going to put the next component here. Again, this one is dependent on time because this component is time dependent and
